<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFFFFBEFF3D9AD66BC07A06" pageId="18" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFFFFBEFF3D9AD66BD37BA8" blockId="18.[151,756,1682,1895]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFFFFBEFF3D9AD668057BCB" bold="true" box="[151,264,1682,1706]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is characterized by elongate test, gently tapering and greatest breadth toward the apertural end.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFFFFBEFF3D9A956BC07A06" blockId="18.[151,756,1682,1895]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFFFFBEFF3D9A9568C57B88" bold="true" box="[151,456,1745,1769]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Taylor age and Navarro age by C USHMAN (1946) in America. It is also recorded in the Upper Cretaceous and Paleocene by LUGER (1985) in Southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="32CB7663FFFFFFBEFE469B746B227A29" box="[492,559,1840,1864]" name="Egypt" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">Egypt</collectingCountry>
. In the study area, it is found in the Maastrichtian-Paleocene sediments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
